# DailyFlow Backend API 

> Smart Goal Planning — REST API built with Node.js, Express, and MongoDB

[![Node.js](https://img.shields.io/badge/Node.js-18%2B-green)](https://nodejs.org)
[![Express](https://img.shields.io/badge/Express-4.x-blue)](https://expressjs.com)
[![MongoDB](https://img.shields.io/badge/MongoDB-Atlas-green)](https://mongodb.com)
[![Render](https://img.shields.io/badge/Deployed-Render-purple)](https://dailyflow-backend-dqou.onrender.com)

---

## Live API

**Base URL:**
```
https://dailyflow-backend-dqou.onrender.com
```

**frontend URL:**
```
https://daily-flow-git-main-isaacsolomon332-cells-projects.vercel.app
```

>  **Note:** This API is hosted on Render's free tier. The server may take **50–60 seconds** to respond on the first request after a period of inactivity (cold start). Subsequent requests will be fast.

---

##  Health Check

Use this endpoint to check if the server is alive paste the url :

```
GET https://dailyflow-backend-dqou.onrender.com/health
```

**Response:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "DailyFlow API is running"
}
```

---


##  Tech Stack

| Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|
| Node.js | Runtime |
| Express.js | Web framework |
| MongoDB Atlas | Database |
| Mongoose | ODM |
| JWT | Authentication |
| Bcryptjs | Password hashing |
| Nodemailer | Email sending |
| Winston | Logging |

---

## Project Structure

```
dailyflow-backend/
└── backend/
    ├── config/
    │   └── db.js               # MongoDB connection
    ├── controllers/
    │   └── authController.js   # Auth logic
    ├── middleware/
    │   ├── auth.js             # JWT protect middleware
    │   ├── validate.js         # Request validation rules
    │   └── errorHandler.js     # Global error handler
    ├── models/
    │   └── User.js             # User schema
    ├── routes/
    │   └── authRoutes.js       # Auth routes
    ├── utils/
    │   ├── email.js            # Nodemailer + email templates
    │   ├── logger.js           # Winston logger
    │   ├── token.js            # JWT sign utility
    │   └── AppError.js         # Custom error class
    ├── app.js                  # Express app setup
    ├── server.js               # Entry point
    └── package.json
```

---

##  API Endpoints

All endpoints are prefixed with `/api/auth`

### Health Check
```
GET /health
```

---

### Signup
```
POST /api/auth/signup
```
**Body:**
```json
{
  "fullName": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "username": "johndoe",
  "phoneNumber": "+2348012345678",
  "password": "secret123",
  "confirmPassword": "secret123"
}
```
**Response:** JWT token + user data
**Email sent:**  Welcome email but not working for now still on progress

---

### Login
```
POST /api/auth/login
```
**Body:**
```json
{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "secret123"
}
```
**Response:** JWT token + user data
**Email sent:**  Login notification email but not working for now still on progress

---

### Get Current User 
```
GET /api/auth/me
```
**Headers:**
```
Authorization: Bearer <your_jwt_token>
```
**Response:** Logged-in user's profile

---

### Forgot Password
```
POST /api/auth/forgot-password
```
**Body:**
```json
{
  "email": "john@example.com"
}
```
**Response:** Generic success message (OTP sent to email)
**Email sent:** 6-digit OTP email (expires in 10 minutes) but not working for now still on progress

---

### Verify OTP
```
POST /api/auth/verify-otp
```
**Body:**
```json
{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "otp": "482910"
}
```
**Response:** Short-lived `resetToken` (15 minutes)

---

### Reset Password
```
POST /api/auth/reset-password
```
**Body:**
```json
{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "otp": "482910",
  "newPassword": "newSecret123",
  "confirmPassword": "newSecret123"
}
```
**Response:** Success message
**Email sent:**  Password changed confirmation email

---

##  Forgot Password Flow

```
Step 1: POST /forgot-password  →  OTP sent to email
Step 2: POST /reset-password   →  verify OTP + set new password 
```

---

## Security Features

- Passwords hashed with **bcryptjs** (12 salt rounds)
- OTP stored as **SHA-256 hash** — never plain text
- OTP expires in **10 minutes**
- Max **5 wrong OTP attempts** before invalidation
- JWT tokens expire in **7 days**
- Generic error messages to prevent email enumeration
- Cannot reuse old password on reset

---

## Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file in the `backend` folder:

```env
# Server
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=development

# Database
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/dailyflow

# JWT
JWT_SECRET=your_super_secret_jwt_key
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=7d
OTP_RESET_EXPIRES_IN=15m

# Email (Brevo/Gmail/Mailgun)
EMAIL_HOST=smtp-relay.brevo.com
EMAIL_PORT=587
EMAIL_USER=your_email@example.com
EMAIL_PASS=your_smtp_password
EMAIL_FROM=DailyFlow <noreply@dailyflow.app>
```

---

## Running Locally

```bash
# Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/dailyflow-backend.git
cd dailyflow-backend/backend

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Create .env file and fill in your values
cp .env.example .env

# Start development server
npm run dev

# Start production server
npm start
```

---

##  Email Notifications

DailyFlow sends beautiful HTML emails for:

| Event | Email |
|---|---|
| Signup |  Welcome email |
| Login | Login notification |
| Forgot password |  OTP code email |
| Password reset |  Password changed confirmation |

